            "question": "A fair coin is tossed 8 times. What is the probability of getting exactly 6 heads?",
            "difficulty": "hard",
            "hasDiagram": false,
            "options": {
                "A": "28.0/2^8",
                "B": "8/2^8",
                "C": "1/2^8",
                "D": "56/2^8"
            },
            "answer": "A",
            "hint": "Use Binomial distribution: nCr * (1/2)^r * (1/2)^(n-r)",
            "solution": "P(X=6) = 8C6 * (1/2)^n = 28.0/2^8.",
            "id": 1
